<h1>1. Global Database Configurations & Entity Standards</h1>
<p>The database tier leverages PostgreSQL as its core relational engine. To implement unified audit trails and security, all classes inherit fields from a base configuration class (<code>BaseEntity.java</code>):</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>UUID Identifiers (128-bit):</strong> Rather than exposing auto-incrementing sequential integers, every entity uses a secure, randomly generated UUID as its primary key.</li>
    <li><strong>Temporal Tracking:</strong> Columns <code>created_at</code> and <code>updated_at</code> track auditing data automatically in UTC offset format using database lifecycle listeners.</li>
    <li><strong>Optimistic Locking:</strong> Every record maintains a <code>version</code> counter, monitored by Hibernate to detect and reject concurrent write anomalies.</li>
    <li><strong>Logical Deletion (Soft Delete):</strong> Record deletions map to an active <code>is_deleted</code> boolean check instead of removing physical rows, protecting operational logs.</li>
</ul>

<h1>2. Entity Dictionary & Schema Definitions</h1>

<h2>2.1. User Profile Directory (<code>users</code>)</h2>
<p>Stores core authentication details, contact channels, and system state flags.</p>
<table border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Column Name</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Constraints</th>
            <th>Operational Description</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Primary Key, Not Null</td>
            <td>Unique system-wide user identifier.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>email</code></td>
            <td>Varchar(255)</td>
            <td>Unique, Not Null</td>
            <td>Login identifier.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>password_hash</code></td>
            <td>Varchar(255)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>BCrypt hashed password credentials.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>phone</code></td>
            <td>Varchar(20)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Mobile line used for WhatsApp OTP verification.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>email_verified</code></td>
            <td>Boolean</td>
            <td>Default false</td>
            <td>True if email verification check is complete.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>phone_verified</code></td>
            <td>Boolean</td>
            <td>Default false</td>
            <td>True if WhatsApp OTP check is complete.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>2.2. Provider Listings & Catalogs (<code>businesses</code> & <code>services</code>)</h2>
<p>Holds operational GPS locations, service radius constraints, and catalog service offerings.</p>

<h3>Table: <code>businesses</code></h3>
<table border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Column Name</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Constraints</th>
            <th>Operational Description</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Primary Key, Not Null</td>
            <td>Unique business identifier.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>owner_id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Foreign Key (users.id)</td>
            <td>Links business to a verified SHOP_OWNER.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>name</code></td>
            <td>Varchar(255)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Registered trade or shop name.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>latitude</code></td>
            <td>Decimal(10,8)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Shop latitude coordinates for GPS matching.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>longitude</code></td>
            <td>Decimal(11,8)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Shop longitude coordinates for GPS matching.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>service_radius_km</code></td>
            <td>Integer</td>
            <td>Default 5</td>
            <td>Range boundary for hyperlocal matching checks.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Table: <code>services</code></h3>
<table border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Column Name</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Constraints</th>
            <th>Operational Description</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Primary Key, Not Null</td>
            <td>Unique service offering identifier.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>business_id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Foreign Key (businesses.id)</td>
            <td>Associated trade shop mapping.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>name</code></td>
            <td>Varchar(255)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Offering title (e.g. Bathroom Jet Cleaning).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>price</code></td>
            <td>Decimal(12,2)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Normal listing catalog price.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>discount_price</code></td>
            <td>Decimal(12,2)</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Actual price charged during checkouts.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>duration_minutes</code></td>
            <td>Integer</td>
            <td>Not Null</td>
            <td>Job time slot estimate in minutes.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>2.3. Accounting & Transactions Ledger (<code>wallets</code> & <code>wallet_transactions</code>)</h2>
<p>Monitors cash values and enforces split fee billing configurations (reserves an 8.5% platform commission and releases 91.5% net value to provider balances upon job complete triggers).</p>

<h3>Table: <code>wallets</code></h3>
<table border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Column Name</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Constraints</th>
            <th>Operational Description</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Primary Key, Not Null</td>
            <td>Unique card wallet ID.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>user_id</code></td>
            <td>UUID</td>
            <td>Foreign Key (users.id)</td>
            <td>Links wallet directly to account owner.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>balance</code></td>
            <td>Decimal(15,4)</td>
            <td>Default 0.0000</td>
            <td>Cash balance (expressed in INR).</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

